'''Jonas Adjei Adjetey''' (born 13 December 2003) is a Ghanaian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for German {{German football updater|Wolfsbur}} side [[VfL Wolfsburg]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]]. He plays mainly in the position of [[centre-back]], but can also play as [[full-back (association football)|full-back]] on either side.

==Club career==
===FC Basel===
Born in [[Accra]], Ghana, Adjetey played his youth football with the local clubs in that area. In 2020 he moved from the youth department of [[Accra Great Olympics F.C.|Great Olympics]] to the youth of [[Berekum Chelsea F.C.|Berekum Chelsea]].

At the end of June 2022 [[FC Basel]] started their new training week with the Ghanaian guest Adjetey, following which he was offered a contract and thereafter joined the U-21 team, who played in the [[Swiss Promotion League|Promotion League]], the third tier of Swiss football.<ref name="4-4-2-FCB-Ajetay">{{cite web | first = Tilman | last = Pauls | author-link = | date = 20 June 2022 | url = https://www.4-4-2.com/super-league/fc-basel/fc-basel-test-ghanaischer-innenverteidiger-jonas-adjei-adjetey/ | title = Der FC Basel testet den ghanaischen Innenverteidiger Jonas Adjei Adjetey | format = | work = | trans-title = FC Basel is testing Ghanaian central defender Jonas Adjei Adjetey | publisher = 4-4-2.com | language = de-ch | access-date = 16 November 2023}}</ref> That Autumn he played 16 of the U-21's 19 matches, then, during the winter break, he was brought up to Basel's first team for the second half of their [[2022–23 FC Basel season]]. However, apart from test matches, he never had any competition appearances with the first team during this time.

Then at the beginning of their [[2023–24 FC Basel season|2023–24 season]] Adjetey played his [[Swiss Cup]] debut for his new team in the away game on 20 August. Adjetey (19) played [[centre-back]] over the full 90 minutes, in a chain of three defenders, with the likewise young Nasser Djiga (20) and Finn van Breemen (20) on his sides. Both Djinga and van Breemen each scored a goal during the first half, as Basel went on to win 8–1 against amateur club FC Saint-Blaise.<ref name="fcb-achiv-2023/24-Cup-St. Blaise-FCB">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv" | author-link = | date = 20 August 2023| url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31826 | title = FC Saint-Blaise - FC Basel 1:8 (1:5) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv" | access-date = 16 November 2023}}</ref><ref name="BZ-2023-Debütantenball-Saint-Blaise-FCB">{{cite web | first = Jakob | last = Weber | author-link = | date = 20 August 2023 | url = https://www.bzbasel.ch/sport/fc-basel/debutantenball-im-jura-ld.2501941 | title = Debütantenball im Jura und weitere Erkenntnisse nach dem 8:1 des FC Basel gegen 2. Ligist Saint-Blaise | format = | work = | trans-title = Debutant party in the Jura and further insights after FC Basel's 8-1 win against 6th division Saint-Blaise | publisher = bz – Zeitung für die Region Basel | language = de-ch | access-date = 16 November 2023}}</ref>

Following this Adjetey returned to the U-21 team, so that he could obtain more playing experience, and he played nine further matches with them. Then, after playing in two test games for the first team, he played his [[Swiss Super League|domestic league]] debut for the club in the home away game in the [[Swissporarena]] on 17 December 2023 as Basel won 1–0 against [[FC Luzern|Luzern]].<ref name="sport.ch-2023/24-Adjetey debüt">{{cite web | first = | last = red. | author-link = | date = 17 December 2023 | url = https://sport.ch/fc-basel-1893/1212040/massive-personalprobleme-bescheren-fcb-youngster-sein-cssl-debuet | title = Massive Personalprobleme bescheren FCB-Youngster sein CSSL-Debüt | format = | work = | trans-title = Massive personnel problems mean FCB youngsters are making their CSSL debut | publisher = sport.ch | language = de-ch | access-date = 17 December 2023}}</ref><ref name="fcb-achiv-2023/24-FCL-FCB">{{cite web | first = | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv" | authorlink = | date = 17 December 2023 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=31844 | title = FC Luzern - FC Basel 0:1 (0:0) | format = | work = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv"}}</ref>

Adjetey extended his contract with [[FC Basel]] until 2028 on 29 August 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|date=28 August 2024|title=Der FCB verlängert mit Jonas Adjetey bis Sommer 2028|url=https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/vertragsverlaengerung-jonas-adjetey|publisher=[[FC Basel]]| language=german}}</ref>

===VfL Wolfsburg===
On 2 February 2026, Adjetey signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfL Wolfsburg]] on a contract until summer 2030, for a undisclosed fee reported to be around €10,000,000.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 February 2026 |title=Wolfsburgs Angebot zu gut: Basel lässt Adjetey zum VfL ziehen |url=https://www.kicker.de/wolfsburgs-angebot-zu-gut-basel-laesst-adjetey-zum-vfl-ziehen-1190051/artikel |access-date=2026-02-03 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref>

==International career==
Adjetey was called up to the [[Ghana national under-20 football team|Ghana U-20]] team for the first time in May 2022, to represent them in the [[2022 Maurice Revello Tournament]].<ref name="GFA-2022-Maurice Revello Squad">{{cite web | first = | last = Ghana Football Association | author-link = | date = 29 May 2022 | url = https://www.ghanafa.org/black-satellites-squad-for-2022-maurice-revello-tournament-in-france | title = Black Satellites squad for 2022 Maurice Revello tournament in France | format = | work = | trans-title = | publisher = Ghana Football Association | language = en | access-date = 16 November 2023}}</ref> He made his debut for them, and played the full 90 minutes, on 30 May 2022 against [[Mexico national under-23 football team|Mexico U-23]].<ref name="tournoimauricerevello-2022-Mexico-Ghana">{{cite web | first = | last = red. | author-link = | date = 30 May 2022 | url = https://www.tournoimauricerevello.com/festival/detail_actualite.php?id=5011 | title = Le Mexique s'impose dans la douleur face au Ghana | format = | work = | trans-title = Mexico wins painfully against Ghana | publisher = tournoimauricerevello.com | language = fr | access-date = 16 November 2023}}</ref> In the tournament's second match against [[Indonesia national under-20 football team|Indonesia U-20]] he came on as substitute.

Adjetey made his [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]] debut on 15 October 2024 in an [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group F|Africa Cup of Nations qualifier]] against Sudan at the [[Benina Martyrs Stadium]] in Libya. He substituted [[Mohammed Salisu]] in the 73rd minute, as Sudan won 2–0.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/commentary/_/gameId/722063|title=Sudan v Ghana game report|date=15 October 2024}}</ref>

In the World Cup qualifiers against Madagascar played in Morocco on 24 March 2025, Adjetey replaced injured Jerome Opoku in the 83rd which Ghana won 3-0.

